
EVALUATION OF 2024 PROMPTING TOOLS ACROSS DIVERSE AI PLATFORMS

AIM

To compare the performance of AI platforms using refined prompting techniques.

OBJECTIVE

* To test multiple prompting methods.
* To compare outputs across AI models.
* To evaluate quality, depth, and accuracy.

AI PLATFORMS TESTED

| Platform       | Specialty                    |
| -------------- | ---------------------------- |
| ChatGPT        | Conversational AI            |
| Claude         | Long-context reasoning       |
| Gemini (Bard)  | Google ecosystem integration |
| Cohere Command | Enterprise NLP               |
| Meta AI        | Open-source LLM ecosystem    |

PROMPTING TECHNIQUES USED

1. Zero-shot prompting
2. Few-shot prompting
3. Chain-of-thought prompting
4. Role prompting
5. Context-aware prompting

TEST SCENARIOS

* Essay generation
* Coding tasks
* Summarization
* Mathematical reasoning
* Creative writing

OBSERVATIONS

| AI Tool | Accuracy  | Creativity | Reasoning |
| ------- | --------- | ---------- | --------- |
| ChatGPT | High      | High       | Excellent |
| Claude  | Very High | Medium     | Excellent |
| Gemini  | High      | Medium     | Good      |
| Cohere  | Medium    | Medium     | Good      |
| Meta AI | Medium    | High       | Medium    |

RESULT

Different prompting styles significantly affected output quality across platforms.


